    "source_sections": {
      "references": "",
      "remarks": "One can also ask this for points in $\\mathbb{R}^3$. In $\\mathbb{R}^4$ Lenz observed that there are $x_1,\\ldots,x_n,y_1,\\ldots,y_n\\in \\mathbb{R}^4$ such that $d(x_i,y_j)=1$ for all $i,j$, taking the points on two orthogonal circles.\n\nMore generally, if $F(2n)$ is the minimal number of such distances, and $f(2n)$ is minimal number of distinct distances between any $2n$ points in $\\mathbb{R}^2$, then is $F =o(f)$?\n\nSee also [89]."
    },
